# Agentic DevOps — environment configuration
# Copy to `.env` (project dir) or `~/.config/agentic-devops/.env` and fill in.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Secrets model — two planes (see docs/security.md § "Secrets model")
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Plane 1 — BOOTSTRAP (this file / your platform's secret injection / IaC).
#    The minimal secrets the platform needs to *come up and be administrable*.
#    They can't be managed from the admin UI — the platform isn't up yet — so
#    they live in the environment. Keep this list SMALL.
#
#  Plane 2 — RUNTIME external-service credentials (the VAULT / admin Secrets tab).
#    Everything Devy reaches out to: LLM provider keys, LangSmith, Tavily,
#    GitHub PATs, host/MCP bearer tokens. These are MASTERED IN THE VAULT
#    (LocalStack in dev, AWS Secrets Manager in prod) and set on the admin
#    Secrets tab — NOT here. The vault is authoritative: if you also set one of
#    these in this file, the proxy logs a warning and the vault value wins.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ═══ Plane 1 — Bootstrap (belongs here) ══════════════════════════════════════

# --- Database (Postgres + pgvector; required — sessions + knowledge base) ---
# The DB connection string (incl. password) is a bootstrap secret: Devy can't
# start without it, so it's injected via the environment, never the admin UI.
# In the bundled docker-compose stack this is set for you (points at `postgres`).
# Set it here to bind a managed instance (RDS/Aurora) or for native runs.
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://agentic:agentic@localhost:5432/agentic
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD=agentic     # compose only: password for the bundled postgres

# --- Admin control plane (optional; enables the /admin UI) ---
# These gate the admin plane itself — you can't set the admin-access secret
# *through* admin access — so they're bootstrap, not vault-managed. Until BOTH
# are set the admin plane stays disabled (endpoints return 503); the assistant
# (chat) plane is unaffected. Generate with: agentic-devops admin set-password
# DEVY_ADMIN_PASSWORD_HASH=$2b$12$...      # bcrypt hash of the admin password
# DEVY_ADMIN_SECRET=...                     # HMAC signing secret (openssl rand -hex 32)

# --- Deploy mode + vault access (bootstrap: how we reach the vault) ---
# DEVY_MODE=dev                             # dev = LocalStack SM (writable) | prod = real AWS SM
# In dev, compose wires LocalStack via AWS_ENDPOINT_URL + dummy AWS_* creds.
# In PROD set DEVY_MODE=prod and grant the task an INSTANCE IAM ROLE — no AWS
# keys at rest. boto3 reads AWS_* / AWS_ENDPOINT_URL from the environment.

# --- Grafana MCP sidecar (optional; only if you mount the Grafana MCP) ---
# Your Grafana tenant URL — NOT a secret, just the endpoint the mcp-grafana
# sidecar reaches. The service-account TOKEN is vault-mastered (Plane 2 below),
# forwarded by the proxy as the request Bearer — it is NOT set here.
# GRAFANA_URL=https://<your-stack>.grafana.net


# ═══ Plane 2 — Runtime secrets (do NOT put here; set on the admin Secrets tab) ═
#
# Mastered in the vault under devy/provider/* and devy/mcp/*, resolved at boot
# (provider keys) or at mount time (MCP bearers). Listed here only so you know
# what NOT to scatter into .env:
#
#   ANTHROPIC_API_KEY   → Secrets tab · devy/provider/anthropic
#   OPENAI_API_KEY      → Secrets tab · devy/provider/openai   (embeddings + chat fallback)
#   GEMINI_API_KEY      → Secrets tab · devy/provider/gemini
#   TAVILY_API_KEY      → Secrets tab · devy/provider/tavily
#   LANGSMITH_API_KEY   → Secrets tab · devy/provider/langsmith
#   HOST_MCP_TOKEN      → Secrets tab · devy/mcp/host  (config.yaml uses secret_ref)
#   Grafana SA token    → MCP tab     · devy/grafana/token  (registry row uses secret_ref;
#                                        proxy forwards it as the Bearer to mcp-grafana)
#   GitHub PATs         → Repos tab   · devy/github/<account>
#
# First-time bootstrap only: `agentic-devops secrets set devy/provider/openai <value>`
# writes straight into the vault from the CLI (dev, LocalStack).
#
# NOTE — the host-MCP *server* (the deployable sidecar / compose `host-mcp`
# service) is a standalone package with no vault client, so IT still reads its
# own HOST_MCP_TOKEN from the environment / its token file — that's the server's
# own credential, provisioned to match the vault master. Keep HOST_MCP_TOKEN in
# the repo-root .env ONLY for that server; the proxy resolves its copy from the
# vault (devy/mcp/host).


# ═══ Optional scalar overrides (defaults shown) ══════════════════════════════
# AGENTIC_DEVOPS_HOST=127.0.0.1
# AGENTIC_DEVOPS_PORT=8765
# AGENTIC_DEVOPS_DEFAULT_TIER=balanced
# AGENTIC_DEVOPS_MAX_ITERATIONS=12
# AGENTIC_DEVOPS_TRACING=jsonl            # jsonl | langsmith | none

# Point at a non-default operator config file (otherwise
# ~/.config/agentic-devops/config.yaml is used if present):
# AGENTIC_DEVOPS_CONFIG=/etc/agentic-devops/config.yaml
